CatDescriptText: Mrs. Catherine Johnson, 2427 Libbie Street, was part of the Pittsburghers Speak Up column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 8, 1958, pg. 2 with question: "Should jitney drivers be licensed and permitted to operate, or should they be jailed?" answer reads: "Because many times you cannot get a cab, they (jitneys) should be licensed."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Catherine Johnson wearing patterned head scarf and dark single button Persian lamb coat, standing in front of sign that reads "Sp... In...Choi..."  and store window with pipe display that reads "Kaywoodie"
